The paper proposes an end-to-end detection system for mitotic nuclei identification in breast cancer histopathological images using deep object detection-based Mask R-CNN. The paper involves computer vision techniques for object detection and deep learning for classification, which are the main focus of the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for classification and detection, which are the main focus of the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of deep learning models for image retrieval, which is the main focus of the cs.IR sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models for object detection, which is the main focus of the cs.DL sub-category.
